  "prompt": "What is the most used word in Malayalam?",
  "response": "In Malayalam, like in many languages, the most frequently used words are typically small, functional words such as:\n\n1. \"\u0d09\u0d33\u0d4d\u0d33\" (ulla) - meaning \"is\" or \"exists\"\n2. \"\u0d12\u0d30\u0d41\" (oru) - meaning \"a\" or \"one\"\n3. \"\u0d15\u0d4a\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d4d\" (kondu) - a particle used to indicate means or cause\n4. \"\u0d07\u0d24\u0d4d\" (ith) - meaning \"this\"\n5. \"\u0d05\u0d24\u0d4d\" (ath) - meaning \"that\"\n\nHowever, the exact most used word can vary depending on the context (spoken language, written text, literary work, etc.). To definitively determine the most used word would require a comprehensive corpus linguistic study analyzing a large collection of Malayalam texts.",
